<item>
            <title>[LU-16445] Make nodemap root squash independent of map_mode</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16445</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a nodemap has &lt;tt&gt;map_mode=projid&lt;/tt&gt;, only projid is mapped. So even if the &lt;tt&gt;admin&lt;/tt&gt; property is set to 0, user root (0:0) will remain as-is.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push a patch to change this behavior and have root user squashed if &lt;tt&gt;admin&lt;/tt&gt; is set to 0, independently of the &lt;tt&gt;map_mode&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
